sion\n-- public redaction: no extra public-web redaction layer beyond baseline\n-  `but-agentlog` redaction\n-\n-Deferred until implementation:\n-\n-- exact projection payload returned from `but-agentlog` to Forge\n-- exact dedupe behavior when a session matches both review and branch targets\n-- refresh and invalidation behavior for cached snapshots\n-- detailed no-data and weak-evidence page copy\n-- initial UI wireframe and interaction details\n+## Failure States\n+\n+V1 should distinguish \"we looked and found nothing\" from \"we could not look.\"\n+\n+Minimum page states:\n+\n+- invalid URL: show that only GitHub pull request URLs are supported\n+- public PR not found or GitHub lookup failed: fail closed and ask the user to\n+  retry later\n+- private repository: explain that v1 only supports public repositories\n+- fork pull request: explain that fork PRs are not supported in v1\n+- metadata ref missing: say no Agent Trail metadata was found for this public PR\n+- metadata found but no matching sessions: say metadata exists, but no related\n+  agent sessions matched the PR review target or head branch\n+- weak branch-only matches: show them separately as possible evidence\n+- fetch/read error: show a retryable error without implying no agent work exists\n+- too much data: show truncated results and keep exact drill-down bounded\n+\n+## Resolved For MVP\n+\n+The buildable v1 path is:\n+\n+```text\n+GitHub PR URL -> GitHub public PR lookup -> repo cache -> fetch refs/meta/main\n+-> but-agentlog review+branch lookup -> generated snapshot -> overview page\n+-> session/turn drill-down\n+```\n+\n+Resolved decisions:\n+\n+- stable PR route renders or generates the latest snapshot in place\n+- immutable snapshot id stays internal for v1\n+- public repository plus publicly fetchable `refs/meta/main` is enough to render\n+  an Agent Trail page\n+- PR number maps to the `but-agentlog` review target\n+- PR head branch is the only fallback target\n+- review-target matches 